No breakfast and snack at dinner
Experts draw attention to the fact that some basic details such as a small family lunch at the same time are needed for healthy development.
In Czech Republic, only 23% of the families of students eat at the same time.
In most families each takes its own breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that's been discovered is that a tenth of the population doesn't take all breakfast.
However, breakfast is the basis for a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in the families of obese children, there was more consumption of malpractice.
Almost every student - without talking about weight - drinks every day of sweet drinks (70%).
More than 40% of the children in question are sports regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare Your Food
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food from opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children from 12 to 15 years of age are far from the ideal for healthy food."
Among their favorite dishes there are many cakes, meats and sugars.
"The most alarming is, in particular, a great preference for sweet lemonades," the results of the investigation are indicated.
For lunch these are the pasta that took the first place just in front of the white meat.
Children did not really want feculents and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Head of Health
The survey also showed that children are willing to change their habits from the time they receive ad hoc information.
"In the course of an inspection of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obsence is not an accident", we were told a determined will to go to healthy food," the results of the survey indicated.
The most striking was, for example, with regard to sweet lemonades because children started giving preference to drinking water.
Children have the most frequently cooked white meat and fish as the main dish on the questionnaire and would reduce the sugars and "knedliky" (Czech specialty of bread flour cakes or potatoes).
