The typical course of a Czech trip was at this time to bring with it its own preserved food, sauce, etc.... to save.
Another important moment has also been the interchangeability of the Czech crown that has finally allowed our tourists after decades of free purchasing power from the Western currency.
Our standard of living, as well as the average wage, have increased what has led to another important moment around 1997.
As a result of a growing demand for travel, travel agencies have since 1997 started to prepare tours with air charter connections that have greatly reduced costs compared to what was before.
