The option of "vote by vote" is a reality with regard to the electoral process this year in Michoacán, where according to the data highlighted by the Preliminary Electoral Results (PREP) Program, the difference between the first and second seats of the governor's election is only 27 per cent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 out of the 6 thousand 74 total votes.
