It will be recalled that Michoacán has not approved either his Constitution or his Electoral Code of State or his Electoral Justice Act, at the same time that the Congress of State approved the reforms shortly before the end of the legal period so that this electoral process can enter into force and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel has failed to publish it within the time limits provided for by the Law of the Official Journal of the State, with the argument that he had some objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional dispute promoted by the Local Legislative Power and qualified as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the State Representative for Constitutional Reforms, because he did not have the right to "sanction or challenge them".
Interviewed on the possibility of "vote by vote", María de los Ángeles Llenderal said that through the approval of the relevant guidelines by the General Council of the EMI, partial and total counting of votes by the local electoral body would be possible.
Thus, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may be that: the results of verbatim records do not coincide; there is no record of vote and there is no record of vote in the urn file at the chairman of the poll; or there are obvious errors or alterations in verbatim records.
In addition, the total deduction of votes received in all polling stations may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the alleged candidate in the respective election and the candidate in the second ballot is equal to or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition by the party representative and/or coalition who submitted the second of the candidates reported.
The total counting of the vote may also be made if at the end of the common counting it follows that the difference between the candidate alleged to be winning and that of the second place is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is an express request from the representative of the political party to which the candidate is issued, in which case the electoral packages which have been the subject of the partial counting shall be excluded.
It should be noted that this is the situation of Morelia's election, where according to the PEP, the difference between the first and second seats is only 0.16 per cent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total verbatim records.
