After reaching the goal of gathering 500 or 600 minors, the study will continue in the Sports Unit Independent (South of Federal District) and finally in the Sports Unit Morelos (North of Federal District).
He explained that the purpose of this research and the purpose of this research was to identify the components and importance of genetics in terms of the development of obesity and to identify risk factors for children and young Mexicans to prevent chronic degenerative diseases.
As World Diabetes Day will be held on 14 November, he mentioned that the goal is to bring together three thousand children and young people between six and 14 years of age, with the consent and under the supervision of their parents, for the application of specific food-related questionnaires.
