So was the work of Cali's person who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A touchyloscopist from Cali was passed on to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano'.
The work of these officials is crucial.
Last November 4 a Dactyloscope of the Cali ITC passed to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Chief of Farc: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his digital prints.
Seven dactyloscopes working in the local ITC offices this week were the "availability" tour of Eliaszar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to Valle's capital and after having attended appropriate courses, he specialized in dactyloscope, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. paupes and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eleazar was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something really big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to take the map with the ten digital prints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the place of the body, he did not recognize it by his physical appearance, because it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed as a farmer in the area, with no glasses and much more thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian wolf, an encre, a kidnapper and a lantern, Eliezer compared the digital prints of the body to those of the map.
His eye did not deceive him; it was "Alfonso Cano".
That very night, the man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for confirming to the Minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that yes, he was the Supreme Chief of the Farc.
Looking for the print
For a touchyloscopist from Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave to Eliasar González at a press conference for the operation against "Cano" is very significant.
A lot of people didn't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without mistake, which can be crucial in the crime resolution.
Apart from identifying the bodies, the dactyloscopes support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many offenders have false identity cards or no documents.
We take their digital prints and search the database.
The researcher found that in a case of flight he had to remove a part of a wall from a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to make out a chest full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to print a digital print, but in this case we were able to get the whole handprint and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
Prints may also remove or confirm suspects in cases of murder.
We recently found a dead man with drinking bottles around him.
Through the investigation, it was determined that a parent could be suspected of the crime and indeed a print on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee that he's the killer, it puts him on the scene of the crime.
A ITC dactyloscope explained that "digital prints of objects with chemical or physical reactives" were extracted.
When they appear, a picker or a band is used to pick them up.
Later, the prints are sent to Asif, the trigger database, or to the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still a lot of paperless Colombians," said the ITC expert.
He explained that everything is not how it is shown in the CSI TV program.
As everything that shines isn't gold, everything we touch doesn't necessarily become a print.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
